.<img data-lazy-fallback="1" decoding="async" width="1200" height="699" class="wp-image-1910207" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Kwankwaso.png" alt="Kwankwaso" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Kwankwaso.png?width=1200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1200w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Kwankwaso-300x175.png?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Kwankwaso-1024x596.png?width=1024&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1024w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Kwankwaso-768x447.png?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px"  /> Dr Rabiu Kwankwaso, the Presidential candidate of the New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) is to address the people of South-West region on his political ambition on Tuesday in Ibadan. Kwankwaso is to feature at a Presidential parley organised by the South-West Development Stakeholders Forum (SWDSF) This is contained in a statement signed by the SWDSF Spokesperson, Olalekan Ajia, on Sunday in Ibadan. Ajia said that Kwankwaso would address the people on how he intends to support the region in executing his existing blueprint for an integrated railway system, power infrastructure and security. He said that the NNPP presidential candidate would also speak on the development of mineral resources to allow for maximum exploration of the region’s abundant human and natural resources. According to him, everything the presidential candidate would speak on are in line with the programmes spelt out by the Development Agenda for Western Nigeria (DAWN). The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the forum had earlier hosted Mr Kola Abiola of the Peoples Redemption Party (PRP) and Mr Omoyele Sowore of African Action Congress (AAC). NAN reports that the forum is scheduled to take place on Tuesday, Jan. 31 at the Jogor Events Centre in Ibadan. Also, among those who have attended the forum were Prince Adewole Adebayo of the Social Democratic Party and Alhaji Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Ajia said that the SWDSF through its Chairman, Mr Alao Adedayo, has sent fresh invitations to Sen. Bola Ahmed Tinubu of All Progressives Congress (APC) and Mr Peter Obi of the Labour Party (LP) to feature at the programme on Tuesday when it would end. Meanwhile, a renowned Veteran and Award-winning filmmaker, Tunde Kelani, has thrown his weight behind the SWDSF and announced his membership of the forum. Kelani, popularly known as TK, attributed his success in life to a solid foundation laid by the Western region government led by the late Chief Obafemi Awolowo and assisted by the late Chief S.L Akintola among others. He described as sad and disheartening the reality that the Yoruba have lost their enviable glory today. “The time and opportunity to serve has come with SWDSF. I hope it is not just a forum, but a platform for action,’’ Kelani said.   Convener of Concerned Nigerians and rights activist, Deji Adeyanju has urged the Labour Party, LP, Presidential candidate, Peter Obi and his counterpart in the New Nigeria Peoples Party, NNPP, Rabiu Kwankwaso to pair up as a team to defeat the two prominent political parties, All Progressives Congress, APC, and Peoples… In "News" By Adeola Badru  The Presidential Candidate of the New Nigeria Peoples Party, NNPP, Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, will be addressing people of the South West on Tuesday, January 31, 2023 at the Presidential Parley being organised  by the South West Development Stakeholders Forum (SWDSF), at Jogor Centre, Ibadan.  The NNPP flagbearer,… In "News" The Presidential candidate of the New Nigerian People Party (NNPP) Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso has commissioned his presidential campaign office in Kano and he describes his party as the fastest-ever growing political party in Nigeria. In "Politics"